Tunisia's President Beji Caid Essebsi was readmitted to the hospital this week after suffering a second health scare in a month, his son has said. Essebsi reportedly suffered from the effects of his previous health scare. He spent a week in hospital last month (June) over a "severe health crisis". He has only appeared in public twice since leaving the hospital for the first time at the beginning of July. The presidency announced Essebsi's death on their official Facebook account on Thursday. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 